4 Section 3. Section 44-7-303, MCA, is amended to read:
5 "44-7-303. Restorative justice fund created -- source of funding -- use of fund. (1) There is an
6 account in the state special revenue fund established by 17-2-102 to be known as the restorative justice fund.
7 (2) There must be deposited in the account:
8 (a) money received from legislative allocations;
9 (b) a transfer of money from a state or local agency for the purposes of 44-7-302;
10 (c) a gift, donation, grant, legacy, bequest, or devise made for the purposes of 44-7-302; and
11 (d) money received by the department of justice for the purpose of administering 46-15-411(2).
12 (3) Except as provided in subsection (2)(d), the fund may be used only to provide grants for
13 restorative justice programs as provided in 44-7-302 to community-based, including faith-based, organizations."
14
15 Section 4. Section 46-15-411, MCA, is amended to read:
16 "46-15-411. Payment for medical evidence -- alleged sexual offenses. (1) The local law
17 enforcement agency within whose jurisdiction an alleged incident of sexual intercourse without consent, sexual
18 assault, or incest occurs shall pay for the sexual assault medical forensic examination of a victim of the alleged
19 offense when the examination is directed by the agency or when evidence obtained by the examination is used
20 for the investigation, prosecution, or resolution of an offense.
21 (2) (a) (1) The department of justice shall, as long as funds are available from an appropriation
22 made for this purpose, pay for the sexual assault medical forensic examination of a victim of an alleged incident
23 of sexual intercourse without consent, sexual assault, or incest if the cost is not the responsibility of a local law
24 enforcement agency under subsection (1).
25 (b) (a) In administering the provisions of this subsection (2)(a) (1), the department shall:
26 (i) identify priorities for funding services, activities, and criteria for the receipt of program funds;
27 (ii) monitor the expenditure of funds by organizations receiving funds under this section;
28 (iii) evaluate the effectiveness of services and activities under this section; and
